summary: This document contains instructions for completing an account transfer form, detailing the necessary information and steps required for transferring assets between financial organizations. It includes sections on receiving firm information, transferring account information, and retirement plan restrictions.
keyFacts: The document provides detailed instructions for completing an account transfer form.
It specifies that a recent statement must be attached to process the account transfer.
The document outlines various types of transfers, including direct mutual fund transfers and retirement plan transfers.
It mentions that liquidation instructions will only be accepted from non-NSCC firms.
The form must be signed and dated within 90 days of receipt.
